In this work, we found a general definition of interaction energy for 2-interacting fermions. First, we had examined two Dirac particles interacting with their central potential before we derived two-body Dirac equation in (2 + 1) space-time geometry. For solution of this equation, we separated center of mass and relative coordinates by using explicit form of the equation. Then, we obtained 1st order coupled radial differential equation set. Since the masses of an electron and a hole are very small (m1 and m2), we neglected \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
