				\begin{document}$${M}_{2}^{2}$$\end{document}M22 values in our equations. The solution of 2-interacting fermions in our model indicates that one can obtain general definition for an interaction energy including quantum numbers. We apply our model to an exciton and found its binding energy which is very close to results found in literature. Moreover, since we work in 2 + 1 dimensions, our results do not include any other effects for a monolayer medium. Finally, we calculated the decay time of an exciton (~ps) directly because the interaction energy in our calculations possesses imaginary part.
